# Centralize brand config and copy

Treat this repo as a rebrandable template.

- Prefer putting brand copy and data in `src/constants/index.js` (or a single brand config module) rather than hardcoding strings across many sections.
- Sections in `src/sections/*` should reference constants/config for:
  - brand/project name
  - hero headline/subtext
  - CTAs (button labels)
  - support email/phone
  - footer blurb + link groups

## Repo references (examples)
- Primary data hub: `src/constants/index.js` (nav links, products, footer links, social icons)
- Nav consumes constants: `src/components/Nav.jsx`
- Sections with brand copy to prefer centralizing:
  - `src/sections/Hero.jsx`
  - `src/sections/Footer.jsx`

## When hardcoding is acceptable
- Only for short, purely presentational strings that are unlikely to change across brands.
- If you do hardcode, ensure it contains **no old brand references**.
